  "prompt": "Facebook: What is the revenue model of Facebook?",
  "response": "Facebook, now part of Meta Platforms Inc., primarily generates revenue through a **targeted advertising model**, which accounts for over 90% of its income. Here's a breakdown of its revenue streams:\n\n### 1. **Advertising Revenue (Core Model)**\n   - **Targeted Ads**: Facebook uses vast user data (interests, demographics, behavior) to enable advertisers to reach specific audiences. This includes ads in News Feed, Stories, Instagram, Messenger, and WhatsApp.\n   - **Auction System**: Advertisers bid for ad placements in real-time auctions. Costs are based on metrics like **cost-per-click (CPC)** or **cost-per-impression (CPM)**.\n   - **Ad Formats**: Diverse formats such as video ads, carousel ads, sponsored posts, and dynamic product ads.\n   - **Cross-Platform Reach**: Ads extend across Meta's ecosystem (Facebook, Instagram, Messenger, WhatsApp) and third-party apps/websites via the **Facebook Audience Network**.\n\n### 2. **Consumer Hardware Sales**\n   - Sales of VR hardware (Oculus/Meta Quest) and smart displays (Portal). This is a smaller but growing segment as Meta invests in the metaverse.\n\n### 3. **Fees and Transaction Revenue**\n   - **Marketplace**: Charges fees for sales in certain categories (e.g., vehicles, rentals).\n   - **In-App Purchases**: Takes a 30% cut from digital purchases in apps/games on Facebook (e.g., through Facebook Pay).\n\n### 4. **Enterprise Solutions**\n   - **Workplace by Meta**: Subscription-based collaboration tool for businesses.\n   - **WhatsApp Business API**: Charges businesses for messaging customers at scale.\n\n### 5. **Other Services**\n   - **Meta Verified**: Subscription service for verification badges and premium features (piloted in select regions).\n   - **Developer Fees**: Historical revenue from game developers (e.g., via Facebook Gaming), though less significant today.\n\n### Key Strengths\n   - **Data-Driven Targeting**: Leverages user data to offer highly effective ad personalization.\n   - **Scale**: Billions of active users across platforms ensure massive reach for advertisers.\n   - **Diverse Ad Products**: Continuous innovation in ad formats (e.g., Reels, AR ads).\n\n### Challenges\n   - Privacy regulations (e.g., GDPR, iOS tracking changes) impacting data collection.\n   - Competition from TikTok, Google, and emerging platforms.\n   - Public scrutiny over content moderation and data practices.\n\nIn summary, Meta\u2019s revenue model centers on **advertising**, with ancillary income from hardware, transactions, and enterprise services. Its dominance relies on leveraging user engagement and data to maintain its position as a digital advertising leader.",
